
<item rdf:about='http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-alvarez-mpls-ldp-color-lsp-00.txt'>
    <title>"Signaling Color Label Switched Paths Using LDP", Santiago Alvarez, Kamran Raza, Sami Boutros</title>
    <link>http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-alvarez-mpls-ldp-color-lsp-00.txt</link>
    <description>This document describes extensions to the Label Distribution Protocol (LDP) to signal a switching preference in the presence of multiple paths.  A label switched router (LSR) can associate locally a color with one or more downstream paths or links, and signal a label path per color to upstream LSRs.  Based on local policy, LSRs can select between these color LSPs to implement a forwarding preference on a downstream LSR.  An egress LSR may influence the signaling decision of other LSRs by signaling interest in specific colors.</description>
    <dc:date>2013-07-10T22:00:00-00:00</dc:date>
</item>
